08/08/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Retired General Lyuben Petrov, a former member of the Bulgarian Socialist Party (BSP) and former chief of the Bulgarian Army's general staff, announced plans Monday (7 August) to lead a new radical left party.
He said the party would not support a second term for the BSP's Georgi Parvanov in the October presidential election.
(Dnevnik, Novinar - 08/08/06)
